{"parentUuid":"4c76f5b9-ea1c-4a1d-baed-0dca67eef328","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/appSemPararv3","sessionId":"9d110bb2-9644-4788-862d-b3784dd76b5d","version":"2.1.19","gitBranch":"develop","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-5-20251101","id":"msg_012BUksiSrFpUE1ZoqhVWDqc","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"To create a patch file from a specific commit, use `git format-patch`:\n\n```bash\ngit format-patch -1 97e83ea39c272ff46dfb464af0e5e29125b8e292\n```\n\nThis creates a `.patch` file in the current directory with the commit changes.\n\n**Other useful variations:**\n\n```bash\n# Output to a specific file\ngit format-patch -1 97e83ea39 --stdout > my-changes.patch\n\n# Create patch with a custom output directory\ngit format-patch -1 97e83ea39 -o /path/to/patches/\n\n# Using git diff (simpler format, without commit metadata)\ngit diff 97e83ea39^..97e83ea39 > changes.patch\n```\n\n**To apply the patch later:**\n\n```bash\n# For format-patch output (includes commit info)\ngit am < file.patch\n\n# For diff output (just applies changes)\ngit apply file.patch\n```\n\nWould you like me to create the patch file for you?"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":8780,"cache_read_input_tokens":10359,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":8780,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":4,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CXqNNsJVgzryjgKwGd5pd","type":"assistant","uuid":"2a1cd5c1-ac62-48cd-a14b-537b8ba1ec37","timestamp":"2026-02-05T18:08:41.812Z"}
