{"parentUuid":"3398243b-1340-47cf-b6c8-29dc34727607","isSidechain":false,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/anotonio.silva/dev/appSemPararv3","sessionId":"9d110bb2-9644-4788-862d-b3784dd76b5d","version":"2.1.19","gitBranch":"develop","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-5-20251101","id":"msg_01UFZ2gakP75VyYEUFX3EMwM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `-1` flag tells `git format-patch` to generate a patch for **only 1 commit** starting from the specified commit.\n\nYou can change the number to include more commits:\n\n```bash\n# Patch for the last 3 commits from that point\ngit format-patch -3 97e83ea39\n\n# Patch for the last 5 commits\ngit format-patch -5 97e83ea39\n```\n\nEach commit generates a separate `.patch` file, numbered sequentially (e.g., `0001-commit-msg.patch`, `0002-commit-msg.patch`, etc.).\n\n**Alternative syntax without `-n`:**\n\n```bash\n# From commit A to commit B (exclusive of A)\ngit format-patch A..B\n\n# From a commit to HEAD\ngit format-patch 97e83ea39..HEAD\n```"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":307,"cache_read_input_tokens":19139,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":307,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"}},"requestId":"req_011CXqNYEf8aqYLcUHLtQH6v","type":"assistant","uuid":"c1d25a3f-7e63-4526-9555-9ff26029ad80","timestamp":"2026-02-05T18:10:47.824Z"}
